## Core Principles and Architecture
core_principles_and_architecture:
  - Use English for all code, comments, and documentation.
  - Follow DRY, YAGNI, and KISS principles. [Software Design Principles](https://www.digitalocean.com/community/conceptual-articles/s-o-l-i-d-the-first-five-principles-of-object-oriented-design)
  - Apply SOLID principles, Clean Architecture, and Domain-Driven Design (DDD). [SOLID Principles](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SOLID)
  - Use Design Patterns (Factory, Singleton, Strategy, etc.). [Design Patterns](https://refactoring.guru/design-patterns)
  - Incorporate CQRS and Event Sourcing for complex business logic. [CQRS Explained](https://martinfowler.com/bliki/CQRS.html)
  - Document architecture with the C4 model. [C4 Model](https://c4model.com/)
  - Implement security, performance, and scalability from the start.

## Naming Conventions
naming_conventions:
  - PascalCase for class names and constructor functions.
  - camelCase for variables, functions, methods.
  - kebab-case for filenames, directories, URL paths. [Naming Best Practices](https://google.github.io/styleguide/)

## Error Handling, Prevention, and Security
error_handling_prevention_security:
  - Centralize error handling (e.g., Try-Catch, Result objects). [Error Handling](https://www.toptal.com/abap/clean-code-and-the-art-of-exception-handling)
  - Ensure input validation and sanitization to prevent vulnerabilities (SQL injection, XSS). [OWASP Input Validation](https://owasp.org/www-community/controls/Input_Validation)
  - Apply ACID properties in databases. [ACID in Databases](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ACID)
  - Use circuit breakers to prevent cascading failures. [Circuit Breaker](https://martinfowler.com/bliki/CircuitBreaker.html)
  - Automate security testing in CI/CD pipelines (SAST, linters). [Security Testing](https://owasp.org/www-community/controls/Static_Code_Analysis)
  - Implement OAuth/JWT for authentication and encrypt data at rest and in transit. [OAuth Guide](https://oauth.net/2/)

## Performance, Optimization, and Scaling
performance_optimization_scaling:
  - Efficient memory management, caching (Redis, CDN). [Cache Best Practices](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Caching)
  - Implement horizontal/vertical scaling, load balancing. [Scaling Techniques](https://aws.amazon.com/architecture/well-architected)
  - Apply lazy loading and pagination for large datasets. [Lazy Loading](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Performance/Lazy_loading)
  - Use profiling tools to identify performance bottlenecks. [Profiling Tools](https://www.jetbrains.com/help/profiler/Performance_Profiling_Overview.html)

## Testing Strategies
testing_strategies:
  - Follow TDD and BDD principles. [TDD Guide](https://martinfowler.com/bliki/TestDrivenDevelopment.html) | [BDD Guide](https://cucumber.io/docs/bdd/)
  - Ensure full test coverage in CI/CD pipelines (unit, integration, end-to-end).
  - Cover edge cases and boundary conditions with automated tests.

## DevOps, CI/CD, and Monitoring
devops_ci_cd_monitoring:
  - Automate CI/CD pipelines, follow the 12 Factor App for cloud-native design. [12-Factor App](https://12factor.net/) | [CI/CD Best Practices](https://www.atlassian.com/continuous-delivery/principles/continuous-integration-vs-delivery-vs-deployment)
  - Use canary releases for risk mitigation. [Canary Releases](https://martinfowler.com/bliki/CanaryRelease.html)
  - Implement logging, distributed tracing, and monitoring alerts. [Distributed Tracing](https://opentelemetry.io/)

## Microservices and API Design
microservices_and_api_design:
  - Microservices should have isolated storage, stateless design when possible.
  - Use message brokers (Kafka, RabbitMQ) for async communication. [RabbitMQ Docs](https://www.rabbitmq.com/)
  - RESTful APIs with versioning, rate limiting, and documentation (Swagger). [REST API Design](https://restfulapi.net/)

## Data Management and Storage
data_management_and_storage:
  - Validate data across all layers, use serialization/deserialization techniques. [Serialization Techniques](https://www.baeldung.com/java-serialization)
  - Cloud-native storage solutions for scalability. [Cloud-Native Storage](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/storage/persistent-volumes/)

## Cost and Resource Optimization
cost_and_resource_optimization:
  - Regularly monitor resource usage, leverage serverless and auto-scaling. [Cloud Cost Optimization](https://aws.amazon.com/architecture/cost-optimization/)

## Collaboration and Development Practices
team_collaboration_and_development_practices:
  - Conduct regular code reviews, encourage pair programming. [Code Review Best Practices](https://google.github.io/eng-practices/review/)
  - Use feature flagging, and maintain up-to-date documentation.

## Internationalization and Localization
internationalization_and_localization:
  - Design with internationalization in mind (RTL support, formatting). [i18n Guide](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Add-ons/WebExtensions/Internationalization)

## Mobile Development Best Practices
mobile_best_practices:
  - Design for offline-first, optimize battery usage.
  - Implement responsive design for multiple screen sizes. [Responsive Design Guide](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Learn/CSS/CSS_layout/Responsive_Design)

## AI, Machine Learning, and Data Science Best Practices (Subdivided)
### Data Handling
data_handling_best_practices:
  - Implement data versioning, feature importance techniques, and proper data splits.
  - Use reproducible research practices. [Data Versioning](https://dvc.org/doc/start)

### Model Development and Monitoring
model_development_and_monitoring:
  - Use MLOps for automation and model deployment. [MLOps Guide](https://ml-ops.org/content/mlops-principles)
  - Implement model monitoring and alerting for performance drift.

### Model Optimization and Ethics
model_optimization_and_ethics:
  - Implement hyperparameter optimization, bias detection, explainable AI. [Explainable AI](https://christophm.github.io/interpretable-ml-book/)

## PyCaret and AutoML Best Practices
pycaret_and_automl_best_practices:
  - Preprocess data before using PyCaret's workflows. [PyCaret Docs](https://pycaret.gitbook.io/docs)
  - Use PyCaret's compare_models for quick evaluation, tune_model for hyperparameter optimization.
  - Implement version control for datasets, model configurations, and trained models.
  - Regularly monitor and evaluate model performance in production. [AutoML Guide](https://cloud.google.com/automl/docs/beginners-guide)

## Cloud-Native Development Best Practices
cloud_native_development:
  - Use containerization (Docker) and infrastructure-as-code (Terraform). [Docker Guide](https://docs.docker.com/get-started/) | [Terraform Best Practices](https://www.terraform-best-practices.com/)
  - Set auto-scaling policies based on application-specific metrics. [AWS Auto Scaling](https://aws.amazon.com/autoscaling/)

## Sustainability Practices
sustainability_practices:
  - Optimize algorithms and reduce energy consumption. [Green Software](https://greensoftware.foundation/)
  - Use renewable energy-friendly cloud providers.

## PHP and Laravel Core
  - Use PHP 8.1+ features when appropriate (e.g., typed properties, match expressions).
  - Follow PSR-12 coding standards.
  - Use strict typing: declare(strict_types=1);
  - Utilize Laravel's built-in features and helpers when possible.
  - Follow Laravel's directory structure and naming conventions.
  - Use lowercase with dashes for directories (e.g., app/Http/Controllers).
  - Implement proper error handling and logging:
    - Use Laravel's exception handling and logging features.
    - Create custom exceptions when necessary.
    - Use try-catch blocks for expected exceptions.
  - Use Laravel's validation features for form and request validation.
  - Implement middleware for request filtering and modification.
  - Utilize Laravel's Eloquent ORM for database interactions.
  - Use Laravel's query builder for complex database queries.
  - Implement proper database migrations and seeders.

## Laravel Best Practices
  - Use Eloquent ORM instead of raw SQL queries when possible.
  - Implement Repository pattern for data access layer.
  - Use Laravel's built-in authentication and authorization features.
  - Utilize Laravel's caching mechanisms for improved performance.
  - Implement job queues for long-running tasks.
  - Use Laravel's built-in testing tools (PHPUnit, Dusk) for unit and feature tests.
  - Implement API versioning for public APIs.
  - Use Laravel's localization features for multi-language support.
  - Implement proper CSRF protection and security measures.
  - Use Laravel Mix for asset compilation.
  - Implement proper database indexing for improved query performance.
  - Use Laravel's built-in pagination features.
  - Implement proper error logging and monitoring.

